'''77 Diamonds''' is an online retailer of diamonds and diamond jewellery based in the United Kingdom, but operating throughout the world. The company claims to have the largest selection of certified natural diamonds in the world. They have been called "one of the most innovative online diamond companies to sell loose and set diamond jewellery in the UK."  <ref name=Niven>Niven, Lisa (2 June, 2009) [http://www.bridesmagazine.co.uk/blog/2009/06/06/02/seventy-seven-diamonds Seventy Seven Diamonds] bridesmagazine.co.uk</ref><ref name=Rogers>Rogers, Sam (12 December, 2011) [http://www.bridesmagazine.co.uk/blog/2011/12/12/seventy-seven-diamonds-launches-colours Colour Diamonds] bridesmagazine.co.uk</ref>

==History==

77 Diamonds was founded by Tobias Kormind, a former investment banker at [[Morgan Stanley]],<ref>Adler, Claire (9 September, 2011) [http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/8906bcc4-d311-11e0-9aae-00144feab49a.html#axzz1vVrhVAn9 Careers: Craftsmanship catches on in unlikely places]</ref> with Vadim Weinig in 2005. Kormind believes precious metal hallmarking could be privatized, just like diamond certification, and says it needs to be quicker, cheaper and offer more outlets.<ref>Adler, Claire (9 September, 2011) [http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/6780db0c-d311-11e0-9aae-00144feab49a.html#axzz1vVrhVAn9 Hallmarking: High metal prices shine a light on ancient guarantee] FT.com</ref> The company takes its name from the date that the first diamond engagement ring was given, when [[Maximilian I, Holy Roman Emperor|Archduke Maximilian I of Austria]] presented one to [[Mary of Burgundy]] in the year 1477.<ref>06 December, 2011 [http://theblondeandthebrunette.com/find-your-sparkle-seventy-seven-diamonds/ Find Your Sparkle: Seventy Seven Diamonds]</ref>

In 2010, 77 Diamonds featured in Vogue's inaugural 'Fashion's Night In' feature, devoted to offering discounts from a selection of the most fashionable online retailers.<ref>1 November, 2010 [http://www.vogue.co.uk/fashions-night-in/participating-retailers Vogue.com's Fashion's Night In]</ref><ref>Bergin, Olivia (1 November, 2010) [http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/news-features/TMG8102512/Get-set-for-Fashions-Night-In.html Get set for <U+2018>Fashion<U+2019>s Night In<U+2019>] fashion.telegraph.co.uk</ref>

==Operations==

77 Diamonds customers either build their own diamond ring, buy rings off the shelf, or even buy loose diamonds.<ref name=Rogers/> Each diamond comes with a certificate of authenticity, which the company<U+2019>s founders, Kormind and Weinig, say is key when it comes to customer confidence. They also believe diamonds will rise above the inflation index.<ref>Platt, Hayley (22 Sept, 2011) [http://uk.reuters.com/video/2011/09/22/internet-diamond-business-rocks?videoId=221786792 Internet Diamond Business Rocks] reuters.com</ref> 77 Diamonds has access to over 70% of the world's [[Diamonds (gemstone)|polished diamonds]] and has the largest selection of certified [[Diamonds|natural diamonds]] in the world.<ref name=Niven/> All of their diamonds are conflict-free and comply with the industry<U+2019>s strict [[Kimberley Process Certification Scheme|Kimberley process]] regulations. <ref>Falk Goldston, N.J. (6 December, 2011) [http://theblondeandthebrunette.com/find-your-sparkle-seventy-seven-diamonds/ Find Your Sparkle: Seventy Seven Diamonds] theblondeandthebrunette.com</ref>

